<subSubSection id="C33440DAFFA3BE3334147C5DFCFC437E" pageId="15" pageNumber="56" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B911351FFA3BE3334147C5DFCFC437E" blockId="15.[264,1323,1294,1881]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B95ACF43FFA3BE3334147C5DFE5D432F" bold="true" box="[264,394,1294,1320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Male frons relatively broad, 1.5–2.0x width of first flagellomere; first flagellomere with yellow base and black apex, postpronotum yellow; hind tibia with 1 
<emphasis id="B95ACF43FFA3BE3330157C64FAF44357" box="[1289,1315,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">av</emphasis>
, apex of mesolobus weakly bifurcate (
<figureCitation id="13150FD4FFA3BE3337A37C0CFCC9437E" box="[703,798,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="16.[264,368,1123,1147]" captionTargetBox="[318,1245,530,1096]" captionTargetId="figure-252@16.[264,1323,499,1120]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 5. Piezura pardalina ssp. shanxiensis Xue, Wang &amp; Wu. A. Male genitalia external structures, posterior. B. Male sternite 5, ventral. (adapted from Xue &amp; Wang, 1999)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5051430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5051430/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="56">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
